The paper focuses on improving the performance of Deep Graph Convolutional Networks, which are commonly used in machine learning tasks such as image classification and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of graph convolutional filters in neural networks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
